{"type":"message","id":"2adc2aad","parentId":"35b279ff","timestamp":"2026-04-12T16:30:21.948Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🌙 **Bedtime Story**\n\nIn 1940, a young Polish doctor named Janusz Godessec was captured by the Nazis and sent to a concentration camp. He was given one job — to sort through the belongings of prisoners as they arrived.\n\nEvery single item people brought with them was supposed to be catalogued and logged. But Janusz saw something in their eyes — the desperate hope that maybe, just maybe, their belongings would somehow reach their families.\n\nSo every night, he started writing letters. He used the names and addresses found on suitcases and mailed letters to families, telling them their loved ones were thinking of them. He saved thousands of names.\n\nHe was caught, of course. But by then, the letters had already gone out. Families across Europe started receiving messages they never expected — proof their people were alive, were thinking of them, were brave.\n\nOne small act of defiance. One doctor's stubborn kindness.\n\nThat's the thing about courage — you don't need permission. You just need to start.\n\nGoodnight, everyone. Sleep well. 🖤"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776011421947}}
